From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Entrpi <entrpi@proton.me>
Date: Tue, 3 Feb 2026 19:11:44 +1100
Subject: [PATCH] arm64: dts: cix: Enable USB-C DisplayPort alt mode on Orion
 O6
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Enable RTS5453 USB-PD controllers (rts5453@30 and rts5453@31) on i2c1
for the O6, which were disabled due to a cdns_role_stop race condition
that is no longer observed on 6.19-rc8.

Restore SMMU stream IDs (iommus properties) for all five display
controllers (dpu0-dpu4). These were commented out to avoid ACE errors,
but with smmu_mmhub already enabled in the board DTS with boot-active
SIDs for DPU1, non-boot DPUs got AXI bus errors when accessing
framebuffer memory without registered stream IDs.

Clean up dead RTS5453 nodes from O6N DTS — the O6N has a single USB-C
port handled by CS32G05 on i2c5 (already enabled), not the dual
RTS5453 layout on the O6.

Together these changes enable the full USB-C DP alt mode signal chain:
USB-C connector -> RTS5453 PD controller -> USBDP combo PHY -> DPTX ->
linlondp DPU -> monitor.
